{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771345502,"nonce":"fQsS+XHWHbnpAYvofRBne/LN8Fw=","title":"bug: Borrower self-registration fails with 500 error","message":"Submitting the borrower self-registration form at /registrieren causes a 500 Internal Server Error.\n\nRoot cause: `BorrowersController#self_create` calls `@borrower.send_confirmation_pending_email` after `@borrower.save` succeeds. Inside that method, `BorrowerMailer.confirm_email.deliver_now` is wrapped in `rescue Exception =\u003e e` which raises `ActiveRecord::Rollback`. However, this Rollback is raised outside any transaction block, so it propagates up as a regular exception and gets caught by ErrorHandling as a 500.\n\nTwo problems:\n1. The Rollback has no effect (not inside a transaction block)\n2. The actual mail delivery exception is swallowed without logging\n\nThe underlying mail delivery failure may be environment-specific (SMTP config), but the error handling is broken regardless. The rescue should either log and re-render the form with the error message, or the email should be sent via a background job.\n\nThis is a pre-existing bug (identical code on main).","files":null}]}